,Not Recommended,259720,9014856,"Posted: 8 February, 2014",all,Be_Proud,"For a game with 10 endings, the game's length and replay value aren't much. That is unless you are like me and squeeze every last bit of a game's 'valued' cost in order to get back its moneys worth.Out of all the endings, only about three of them are worth playing through. Other reviewers claim that the game is a highly intricate, interactive rpg-style simulation, but truthfully it's not so much different than a regular indie rpg game or dating sim; probably a few notches worst.Most of the events are predetermined and are based on the limited selection of options made by everyday decisions. Rather, the interactions are quite bland at best and the action & adventure aspect drastically dulls after the tenth battle of the same-looking monster.In conclusion, if you're looking for an extremely cheap-thrilled visual novel worth 5-10 hours of your time (possibly less), this may be your game. Just know that the story length is very short, and the story itself isn't what you'd call pulitzer prize-winning material. If you do decide to buy the game, get ready as you'll probably be spending more time pressing the skip button and reading white words off a black screen, than anything else.Worth the $15? I think not."
