76561198055528037,Recommended,259720,9035386,"Posted: 9 February, 2014",all,Ownificate,"This game is very enjoyable. The duration of the game is completely dependant on how how play through it. If you read every line of text in the game intently, explore, and think about what you are doing the entire time like I did, you will still probably finish it in ~ 5 hours. But keep in mind that is one playthrough and this game is designed to be multiple replays to see different endings and results from your actions.They are not lying when they say your actions make a difference either. During gameplay, you have a choice of doing things like working, resting, hanging out at a cafe, calling friends, and other things. What you choose to do will affect what happens to the characters and how the story proceeds.But down to my favorite part of reviews, pros and cons.+ Great story. Loved it+ Beautiful artwork. If you don't like anime though, this would be a con.+ Many different endings. I just wanted to keep playing to see how things change+ Limited hand-holding. Its up to you what you should or shouldn't do. This might be bad for some, but I love it.+ Characters are well developed.- Minor gripe, but the writing has more grammar errors than there should be in this sort of game.- Sound definitely needs work, but I just enjoyed my own music while playing.- Despite the limited hand-holding, the actual gameplay kind of started to bore me. It is just clicking various things over and       over.Overall: 9/10. If you like Visual novels, dating sims, or a fun story this is for you. If any of those things annoy you, this is an avoid."
